00:16:59.320 --> 00:17:04.359
nothing or even hurt our ability to predict, they wanted it in the models, right? And that was just

00:17:04.359 --> 00:17:07.800
the nature of the business. We couldn't, we couldn't take it out. So we'd have to make a

00:17:07.800 --> 00:17:11.400
call out and we'd say, this is not significant. We're keeping it in there though, because there's

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:15.800
still inherent value in doing this and so forth. And that's just kind of the same I've dealt with

00:17:15.800 --> 00:17:21.160
with any business leader I've worked with is if there's something they're really passionate about

00:17:21.160 --> 00:17:26.520
and they believe and they know to be true, you kind of have to really pay attention to what it is

00:17:26.520 --> 00:17:31.959
they're looking at and help them understand the full story of it. Like I'm not one to say, well,

00:17:31.959 --> 00:17:36.119
what do you need me to show you? And then show it like that is never going to jive with me.

00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:40.920
But I've also learned not to give like hard pushback and say, no, you're wrong. Like do it

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:44.199
this way. I'm smarter than you. And this is telling us whatever, like that goes nowhere either,

00:17:44.199 --> 00:17:48.439
right? You discredit yourself completely. So understanding where they're coming from,

00:17:48.439 --> 00:17:51.719
why they want, and then trying to find some solution. Usually they have, they come to you

00:17:51.719 --> 00:17:56.119
with, Hey, I have this data. I want to answer it. I want this to answer this question, or we're

00:17:56.119 --> 00:17:59.800
trying to do this thing. I think it's going to help us understand if it's working or not.

00:17:59.800 --> 00:18:03.560
